      tr
        th
        th Mixin (prefix)
        th Class (prefix)
    tbody
      tr
        td The flexbox block
        td #[code +flexbox]
        td #[code .flexbox]
      tr
        td The flex-item element (immediate child)
        td #[code +flexitem]
        td #[code .flexitem]

  br
    
  p.
    In the Codebase flexbox system, all the following options are supported:

  ul
    li Flexitem span
    li Flexitem offseting
    li Flexitem (re)ordering
    li Flexitem centering (horizontally) and/or middling (vertically)

  p.
    #[i Incomplete flexitem "rows"?] No problem. Flexbox "rows" can be incomplete. The last flexitem does not expand to occupy the unused space. No additional "end" classes required.

  p.
    #[i Surplus horizontal flexitems ("columns")?] No problem. Flexitems will automatically wrap if they extend beyond the flexbox container max width. The last flexitem does not expand to occupy the unused space. No additional "end" classes required.

  h3 Flexboxes at different Media Query Breakpoints

  p.
    The Codebase media query breakpoint widths are specified by four #[code !default] variables.

  p.
    Flexboxes can be used with or without specifying breakpoints (and with or without using breakpoint classes). Without breakpoints, the flexitems will be displayed the same (% width) whatever the window width.

  p.
    This means that each flexbox system can have up to five viewport width configurations:

